verbose_text: In addition to the different concentrations of IL-1beta and IL-8, we hypothesized different CSF profiles with higher levels of the pro inflammatory TNF, IL-6 and CCL-2 and lower concentrations of the anti-inflammatory IL-1Ra, IL-4 and IL-10 in the RA patients compared to the FM patients.
evidence: levels of the pro-inflammatory TNF, IL-6 and CCL-2
